## 🛠️ Implemented Components

### 1. Root Configurations & Layout
- **[package.json](file:///c:/Users/sachi/Downloads/rigveda-mvp/package.json)**: Configured with Next.js 16.2.6, React 19.2.4, Tailwind CSS v4, named `vedicdharma-engine@0.1.0`.
- **[tsconfig.json](file:///c:/Users/sachi/Downloads/rigveda-mvp/tsconfig.json)**: Configured TypeScript compilation targets and path mapping.
- **[layout.tsx](file:///c:/Users/sachi/Downloads/rigveda-mvp/app/layout.tsx)**: Added Google Fonts mapping for optimal typography:
  - `Inter` (sans-serif) for system utilities and control elements.
  - `Crimson Pro` (serif) for the English translations and literary text.
  - `Noto Sans Devanagari` (Sanskrit) to ensure perfect rendering of Vedic svaras (accents).
  - Configured `suppressHydrationWarning` on `html` and `body` elements to suppress extension class injection warning mismatches (such as ClickUp classes).
- **[globals.css](file:///c:/Users/sachi/Downloads/rigveda-mvp/app/globals.css)**: Implemented styling variables for warm light paper and dark stone themes, premium custom scrollbars, and golden accent highlight glows.

### 2. Main Landing Page (`/`) with UI/UX Feedback Reforms
- **[page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/sachi/Downloads/rigveda-mvp/app/page.tsx)**: Converted into an interactive client component containing:
  - **Refined Hero Hierarchy**: Swapped image caption text with a tight, direct value proposition: *"A rigorous, open-source digital corpus mapping the evolution of ancient Indic philosophy."*
  - **Sanskrit Shloka Highlight**: Centered Mantra 1.1.1, increasing the font size and wrapping it in an elegant, golden-bordered blockquote block.
  - **Live Demo Sandbox ("Show, Don't Tell")**: Created an interactive sandbox section. Users can click individual words in Mantra 1.1.1 to see the un-sandhied Padapatha form, root lemma, grammatical traits, and literal meanings appear in real-time.
  - **Scannable Paradigm Comparison**: Restructured the text detailing the *Layered Disclosure Model* into a side-by-side card grid highlighting *The Traditional Overhead* (clutter, footnotes, sandhi blocks) vs *The DLIIH Solution* (clean canvas, tactile exploration, on-demand data).
  - **TEI/XML Syntax Display**: Added a dedicated technical section demonstrating academic rigor. Features a tabbed code block toggling between raw **TEI/XML Source** and formatted **JSON Payload**.
  - **Expanded Global Navigation**: Refined the sticky header with clean links: *Home*, *Corpus Viewer*, *Interactive Sandbox*, *TEI/XML Schema*, *Roadmap*, and *GitHub*.

### 3. Rigveda Interactive Viewer (`/texts/rigveda/1/1`)
- **[page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/sachi/Downloads/rigveda-mvp/app/texts/rigveda/[mandala]/[sukta]/page.tsx)**:
  - Dynamically loads and parses the Rigveda dataset from [rv_1_1.json](file:///c:/Users/sachi/Downloads/rigveda-mvp/data/rv_1_1.json).
  - **Reading Canvas (Left/Center)**: Displays the 9 mantras of Rigveda 1.1 in large accented Devanagari. Every single word is clickable.
  - **Philological Inspector (Right Sidebar)**: Clicked words update this panel instantly with their un-sandhied Padapatha form, root lemma, grammatical breakdown pills, and literal meanings.
  - **Commentary Accordion (Bottom)**: Houses tabs for Sāyaṇa's classical Sanskrit commentary (Bhāṣya), metadata (Deity, Rishi, Meter), and CC license information.
  - **Mobile Drawer**: The split pane collapses into an overlay bottom sheet on mobile viewports for fluid mobile navigation.

### 4. DLIIH Scholar AI Chatbot
- **[Chatbot.tsx](file:///c:/Users/sachi/Downloads/rigveda-mvp/app/components/Chatbot.tsx)**: A floating interactive widget with auto-scroll and loading indicators, styled with the dark-stone theme.
- **[route.ts](file:///c:/Users/sachi/Downloads/rigveda-mvp/app/api/chat/route.ts)**: A server-side API handler that returns rich context-aware explanations on terms like *Agni*, *Rishi*, *Gayatri*, *Sayana*, *Rta*, *Purohita*, and *Hotr*.

